ndpoint(user: Authenticated){}\r\n#[get(\"/one\", rank = 2)]\r\npub async fn get_public_endpoint(){}\r\n\r\n#[get(\"/two\")]\r\npub async fn get_protected_endpoint(user: Authenticated){}\r\n```\r\n\r\nA guard takes care of enforcing Authenticated.\r\n\r\nif the guard returns Outcome::Error wrapping NotAuthorized, then the second route for /one will never get called \r\n\r\nIf the guard returns Outcome::Forward, then for /two with no authentication the final result will be NotFound instead of UnAuthorized.\r\n\r\nIf Forward could contain a Error, then the routing could be \"Try and find another matching route. If nothing works, then return this error\"\r\n\r\nSo Forward(NotAuthorized) would represent this case\r\n\r\nTo work around this, you need a dummy catchall route to return 'unauthorized', or mess around with a special fairing.\r\n\r\n\r\nA lot of other webframeworks allow for hooking into routing logic. ","closed_by":{"login":"SergioBenitez","id":1480321,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0ODAzMjE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1480321?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez","html_url":"https://github.com/SergioBenitez","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/1560